OL,3,CThames Water found to be worst
OL,4,Cperforming water company for complaints
OL,6,FCCW chief executive Mike Keil said:
OL,7,F"Households are having to waste far
OL,8,Ftoo much time and energy resolving
OL,9,Fcomplaints, which water companies
OL,10,Fshould be getting right first time.
OL,12,F"Trust in the water sector is already
OL,13,Fbadly fractured and the poor handling
OL,14,Fof complaints will only compound
OL,15,Fpeople's frustration.
OL,17,F"We're particularly concerned to see a
OL,18,Fsignificant rise in complaints from
OL,19,Fcustomers with water meters who are
OL,20,Fquestioning the accuracy of their bill.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/15
